Analysis of Main Target Image  
• Block Count & Layers  
  – There are exactly three blocks in the structure.  
  – They form essentially two “levels”:  
    1) The bottom level has a yellow upright cylinder (with a green upright rectangular block rising behind it).  
    2) Resting on top of that green block is a single orange cylinder lying horizontally.  

• Spatial Relationships  
  – The yellow cylinder stands on the ground. The green rectangular block is positioned so that it shares a vertical edge or face with the cylinder (they touch at their sides).  
  – The orange cylinder rests horizontally across the top of the green block, forming the “cap” over the structure.  

Selection of Required Blocks from Dictionary  
• Needed Blocks  
  – Yellow upright cylinder → Block index 11 (matches the vertical cylinder orientation shown).  
  – Green upright rectangular block → Block index 3 (the vertical green prism).  
  – Orange horizontal cylinder → Block index 7 (the horizontally oriented orange cylinder).  

Assembly Order  
Use the following step-by-step sequence (you may of course place them physically as needed, but this gives a logical build order):  

{
  Step1: "Move block with index 11",
  Step2: "Move block with index 3",
  Step3: "Move block with index 7"
}
